(OUTFITCOMPATIBILITY: COMPUTER VISION PROJECT PROPOSAL REPORT) Tj
T* () Tj
T* () Tj
T* (TECH STACK) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (- Frontend: React, TypeScript, Vite, Tailwind CSS, shadcn/radix UI) Tj
T* (- Backend: Node.js, Express, MongoDB \(Mongoose\), JWT, Multer) Tj
T* (- CV/ML Pipeline: Python, PyTorch, torchvision, NumPy, OpenCV) Tj
T* (- CV Models:) Tj
T* (- `compat_top_bottom.pt` for pair compatibility scoring) Tj
T* (- `B_best_category_tempered.pt` for category fallback on external images) Tj
T* (- `A_best_pattern_clean_colab.pt` for pattern prediction) Tj
T* (- `yolov8n-pose.pt` for auto body visibility and crop guidance) Tj
T* (- Segmentation/Background Removal: rembg/U2Net/ISNet/SegFormer options) Tj
T* (- LLM Explanation Layer: Ollama \(Qwen 2.5\) via deferred `/explain` API) Tj
T* (- Datasets:) Tj
T* (- Polyvore outfits \(disjoint train/valid/test and compatibility metadata\)) Tj
T* (- DeepFashion Category and Attribute Prediction Benchmark \(for category and pattern model) Tj
T* (  training\)) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (ABSTRACT) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (OutfitCompatibility is a computer vision system for evaluating outfit pair compatibility and) Tj
T* (recommending matching clothing items. The project combines deep visual embeddings, category) Tj
T* (priors, foreground-aware visual feature extraction, and pattern analysis to compute a final) Tj
T* (compatibility score. It supports two main use-cases: direct top-bottom compatibility checking) Tj
T* (and single-item recommendation \(top to bottom or bottom to top\). A hybrid retrieval strategy) Tj
T* (prioritizes user wardrobe items and uses Polyvore references as fallback. The architecture is) Tj
T* (designed as a full-stack deployable system with a React frontend, Express backend, and a Python) Tj
T* (inference pipeline. The project uses two datasets with different roles: Polyvore for) Tj
T* (compatibility/retrieval learning and DeepFashion for training the category and pattern) Tj
T* (classifiers integrated in inference. To improve user trust and explainability, the system) Tj
T* (exposes structured score breakdowns and optional natural-language explanations through an) Tj
T* (Ollama-based stylist layer. Current limitations such as LLM latency, out-of-distribution) Tj
T* (category confidence, and first-run cache warmup are identified and included as part of the) Tj
T* (proposed extension plan.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (INTRODUCTION) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (Modern wardrobe assistant systems require more than image classification. Practical adoption) Tj
T* (depends on four properties: visual understanding, compatibility reasoning, response speed, and) Tj
T* (user-facing explainability. This project addresses those needs with a context-free computer) Tj
T* (vision pipeline that can operate on user-uploaded photos and dataset references.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (The system is built to bridge research-style compatibility scoring and production-style API) Tj
T* (behavior. It includes robust preprocessing \(autocrop and foreground masking\), score fusion with) Tj
T* (interpretable components, hybrid recommendation from personal wardrobe plus dataset fallback,) Tj
T* (and frontend modules that present confidence and explanation to non-technical users.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (AIM AND OBJECTIVES) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (AIM) Tj
ET
endstream
