() Tj
T* (Develop a reusable and explainable computer vision pipeline that evaluates outfit compatibility) Tj
T* (and recommends matching clothing pieces in a full-stack application setting.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (OBJECTIVES) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (1. Build a reliable pair-scoring model for top-bottom compatibility.) Tj
T* (2. Support single-image recommendation with automatic direction detection.) Tj
T* (3. Reduce background interference using segmentation and body-aware crop logic.) Tj
T* (4. Integrate category, color, brightness, and pattern signals into a unified score.) Tj
T* (5. Prioritize wardrobe-based recommendations before dataset fallback.) Tj
T* (6. Provide user-readable explanation without modifying core scoring decisions.) Tj
T* (7. Keep implementation self-contained under one repository for reproducible deployment.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (THEORY) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (COMPATIBILITY AS MULTI-SIGNAL FUSION) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (Outfit compatibility is modeled as a weighted combination of learned and handcrafted signals:) Tj
T* (- Learned pair compatibility from embedding-based neural scoring.) Tj
T* (- Type prior from category co-occurrence statistics in training pairs.) Tj
T* (- Color harmony from dominant palette relations.) Tj
T* (- Brightness balance from masked visual metrics.) Tj
T* (- Pattern compatibility from model predictions or fallback heuristics.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (This design reflects the theory that style compatibility is not fully captured by a single) Tj
T* (representation. A robust solution requires both data-driven learning and constrained visual) Tj
T* (rules.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (EMBEDDING-BASED PAIR SCORING) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (Each clothing image is encoded into a feature embedding. Pair interaction is modeled by) Tj
T* (concatenating direct and element-wise interactions between embeddings. A classifier head) Tj
T* (produces a base compatibility probability through a sigmoid output.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (CATEGORY PRIOR PROBABILITY) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (A Laplace-smoothed prior is computed from positive and negative top-bottom pair frequency:) Tj
T* (`T\(tc,bc\) = \(pos + alpha\) / \(pos + neg + 2*alpha\)`) Tj
T* (with `alpha = 1.0`.) Tj
T* (This prior stabilizes scoring for semantically common pairings and acts as a probabilistic) Tj
T* (regularizer.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (VISUAL FEATURE THEORY) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (Foreground-aware metrics are used to reduce background bias:) Tj
T* (- Color harmony is computed from weighted dominant palette matching.) Tj
T* (- Brightness compatibility uses Gaussian penalties on brightness/saturation/contrast) Tj
T* (  differences.) Tj
T* (- Pattern compatibility balances solid-pattern interactions and pattern similarity.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (METHOD) Tj
ET
endstream
