T* (4. RECOMMENDATION STRATEGY) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (- Auto mode infers whether upload is top or bottom.) Tj
T* (- Retrieval shortlist uses embedding cosine similarity.) Tj
T* (- Final rerank applies full compatibility fusion.) Tj
T* (- Hybrid mode fills top results from wardrobe first, then Polyvore fallback.) Tj
T* (- Candidate previews use crop-only policy for cleaner visual relevance.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (5. EXPLAINABILITY STRATEGY) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (- Core score is deterministic and unchanged by LLM output.) Tj
T* (- Explanation runs asynchronously via `/explain` to avoid blocking primary response.) Tj
T* (- Fallback deterministic explanation is used when LLM output is invalid.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (SYSTEM IMPLEMENTATION) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (A. FRONTEND LAYER) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (- `MixMatch.tsx`: uploads top and bottom, calls `/compatibility`, then `/explain`.) Tj
T* (- `GlowUp.tsx`: uploads one item, calls `/recommend`, then `/explain`.) Tj
T* (- `MyWardrobe.tsx`: CRUD wardrobe items and image uploads.) Tj
T* (- Structured result cards show score bands, component bars, and explanation status.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (B. BACKEND LAYER) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (- Express routes: `/compatibility`, `/recommend`, `/explain`, `/wardrobe`, `/feedback`.) Tj
T* (- Multer upload handling with temporary and persistent paths.) Tj
T* (- JWT-based user authentication and route-level user context.) Tj
T* (- Python bridge executes pipeline scripts and sanitizes public response payloads.) Tj
T* (- MongoDB required at startup by project policy.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (C. PIPELINE LAYER) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (- Main engine: `services/pipeline/src/outfit_pipeline/engine.py`.) Tj
T* (- Pair scoring script: `run_pair.py`.) Tj
T* (- Recommendation scripts: `run_recommend.py`, `run_recommend_hybrid.py`.) Tj
T* (- Feature extractor for wardrobe cache/backfill: `run_extract_item_features.py`.) Tj
T* (- Explanation script: `run_explain.py`.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (D. CACHING AND RUNTIME) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (- Embedding cache and type-prior cache reduce repeated heavy computation.) Tj
T* (- Runtime directories are repo-local \(`runtime/uploads`, `runtime/cache`\).) Tj
T* (- Cold-start latency is higher when caches are first built, then decreases.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (E. KNOWN LIMITATIONS \(CURRENT\)) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (1. LLM explanation latency remains a bottleneck for user-perceived responsiveness.) Tj
T* (2. External/OOD category confidence can be low for difficult images.) Tj
T* (3. First-run recommendation can take longer during embedding cache warmup.) Tj
T* (4. Some fairness behaviors still depend on configured heuristics and thresholds.) Tj
ET
endstream
